  "text": "The etcd-io/etcd repository implements a comprehensive client-side retry and timeout policy through multiple interconnected components:\n\n## Client Initialization and Connection Management\nThe entry point is `newClient()` (client/v3/client.go:408) which creates a client by:\n1. Setting up dial options via `dialSetupOpts()` (client/v3/client.go:229) which configures gRPC unary and stream interceptors with retry capability\n2. Calling `dialWithBalancer()` (client/v3/client.go:312) which uses the EtcdManualResolver to balance load across endpoints\n3. Calling `dial()` (client/v3/client.go:319) which establishes the gRPC connection\n4. Performing health checks via `waitForConnection()` (client/v3/client.go:345) using gRPC health check service\n\n## gRPC Retry Interceptor\nThe core retry logic is implemented in:\n- `client/v3/retry_interceptor.go`: Contains `unaryClientInterceptor()` and `streamClientInterceptor()` which wrap gRPC calls with retry logic supporting write-at-most-once semantics\n- `client/v3/retry.go`: Defines retry policies (repeatable vs nonRepeatable) and wrapper clients (RetryKVClient, RetryLeaseClient, RetryClusterClient, RetryAuthClient, RetryMaintenanceClient)\n\nThe retry interceptor implements:\n- `isSafeRetry()` which determines retry eligibility based on error type and RPC method\n- `isSafeRetryImmutableRPC()` for read-only operations (Get) which retries on Unavailable errors\n- `isSafeRetryMutableRPC()` for write operations (Put, Delete, Txn) which only retries on \"no address available\" errors\n- `backoffLinearWithJitter()` for exponential backoff with jitter\n- `waitRetryBackoff()` for implementing the backoff wait between retries\n\n## Endpoint Balancer and Resolution\nEndpoint management and balancing is handled by:\n- `client/v3/internal/resolver/resolver.go`: EtcdManualResolver using gRPC's manual resolver with round-robin load balancing\n- `client/v3/naming/resolver/resolver.go`: etcd-specific resolver builder for service discovery\n- `client/v3/internal/endpoint/endpoint.go`: translateEndpoint() and Interpret() functions convert etcd endpoint formats to gRPC-compatible addresses with server name for TLS validation\n\n## Connection Health Check\n`waitForConnection()` performs health checks during dial using:\n- gRPC Health Checking Protocol (healthpb.HealthClient)\n- WaitForReady option to wait until connection is ready\n- Graceful handling of Unimplemented and FailedPrecondition errors\n\n## Request Timeout Enforcement\nTimeout policies are enforced at multiple layers:\n- `client/v3/config.go`: Configurable DialTimeout, DialKeepAliveTime, DialKeepAliveTimeout\n- `client/v3/options.go`: Default options like defaultWaitForReady (true), defaultUnaryMaxRetries (100), defaultBackoffWaitBetween (25ms)\n- `client/pkg/transport/timeout_transport.go`: NewTimeoutTransport() sets read/write timeouts\n- `client/pkg/transport/timeout_dialer.go`: rwTimeoutDialer wraps connections with timeouts\n- `client/pkg/transport/timeout_conn.go`: timeoutConn enforces read/write deadlines on socket level\n- `client/v3/ctx.go`: withVersion() adds API version metadata, WithRequireLeader() enforces leader requirement\n\n## KV, Watch, and Lease Operations\nOperations are wrapped with retry clients:\n- `NewKV()` (client/v3/kv.go) uses RetryKVClient for Put/Get/Delete/Txn with appropriate retry policies\n- `NewWatcher()` (client/v3/watch.go) implements watch stream with automatic reconnection and retry\n- `NewLease()` (client/v3/lease.go) uses RetryLeaseClient for LeaseGrant/Revoke/KeepAlive\n\n## Backoff Strategy\nThe client implements `roundRobinQuorumBackoff()` (client/v3/client.go:535) which:\n- Retries immediately across quorum members\n- Applies backoff only after attempting all quorum endpoints\n- Uses `jitterUp()` (client/v3/utils.go) to add random jitter preventing thundering herd\n\nThis architecture ensures reliable operation through transient failures while maintaining write-at-most-once semantics for mutable operations."
}

